uage of popular culture and everyday life, subverting the official Malay of the Dutch authorities. Through his readings of Sino-Malay print culture published between the 1910s and 1940s, Hoogervorst highlights the inherent value of this vernacular Malay as a language of the people.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aChinesezIndonesiaxHistoryy20th century. 0aLanguage and culturezIndonesiaxHistoryy20th century. 0aLanguages in contactzIndonesiaxHistoryy20th century. 0aLiterature and societyzIndonesiaxHistoryy20th century. 0aMalay literaturezIndonesiaxChinese influences. 0aPopular literaturexPublishingzIndonesiaxHistoryy20th century. 0aPopular literaturezIndonesiaxChinese influences. 0aPrintingzIndonesiaxHistoryy20th century. 4aAnthropology. 4aLanguage Arts & Linguistics. 7aHISTORY / Asia / Southeast Asia.2bisacsh  aStudying history/culture through language, History of Malay, Chinese-Indonesian literature, role of language in popular culture, Southeast Asia in colonial times.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073908408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2021 Englishz978311075408708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2021z9783110753851oZDB-23-DEG40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501758256?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501758256423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501758256/original  a978-3-11-073908-4  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBO